In this proclamation issued by President Donald J. Trump, he declares May 2019 as Older Americans Month. He acknowledges the contributions and sacrifices made by older Americans to the country. The proclamation highlights the ways in which older Americans enrich our lives through their wisdom, guidance, and selfless service. The administration is working to improve the quality of life for seniors by countering fraud, lowering prescription drug prices, and protecting Medicare and Social Security. President Trump calls upon all Americans to honor and care for older Americans and reaffirm the country's commitment to them.